OF STATUTORY RAPE.

02:31.281 --> 02:33.805
-HOBIE...
-I KNOW WHAT RAPE IS, DAD.

02:33.936 --> 02:36.721
-YEAH, I KNOW YOU DO.
JUST WAIT FOR ME UPSTAIRS,
WILL YA?

02:36.852 --> 02:38.114
-OKAY.

02:38.245 --> 02:39.637
I'M SURE EDDIE DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG.

02:41.422 --> 02:42.292
-COME ON AND SIT DOWN.

02:49.734 --> 02:51.867
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS IS HAPPENING.

02:53.999 --> 02:56.350
-GARNER SAY ANYTHING ABOUT
THE GIRL WHO FILED
THE COMPLAINT?

02:56.480 --> 02:58.090
-NO.

02:58.221 --> 02:59.570
-[SIGHS]

03:00.571 --> 03:02.573
YOU KNOW, YESTERDAY,

03:03.400 --> 03:06.751
I FOUND A GIRL'S BATHING SUIT
IN EDDIE'S TOWER.

03:08.362 --> 03:10.277
HE SAID... [EXHALES]

03:10.407 --> 03:13.410
SHE ASKED HIM TO LET HER
CHANGE IN THERE...

03:14.194 --> 03:15.499
THE DAY BEFORE.

03:17.806 --> 03:19.808
SOMEBODY HE PULLED OUT OF WATER.

03:21.766 --> 03:24.508
-WAS IT A ONE-PIECE
BATHING SUIT?
BLACK AND GRAY.

03:25.640 --> 03:27.337
-YEAH.
-OH.

03:27.468 --> 03:28.643
THE TROPHY HUNTER.

03:30.384 --> 03:31.907
I KNEW IT.

03:32.037 --> 03:33.256
-WAS SHE UNDERAGE?

03:33.387 --> 03:35.693
-SIXTEEN.
SEVENTEEN AT THE MOST.

03:36.607 --> 03:37.608
-SHE A REGULAR OUT THERE?

03:37.739 --> 03:39.219
-A NEW COMER.

03:40.785 --> 03:42.570
-PROBABLY WANTED TO GET NOTICED.

03:42.700 --> 03:44.006
-MITCH, I WARNED HIM.

03:44.136 --> 03:45.616
I TOLD HIM WHAT SHE WAS AFTER,

03:45.747 --> 03:47.792
AND HE TOLD ME
I WAS BEING JEALOUS.

03:48.445 --> 03:49.838
I KNEW IT.

03:56.714 --> 03:59.761
-WE'VE GOT A SWORN STATEMENT
FROM CAROLINE LARKIN
THAT YOU GOT HER DRUNK

03:59.891 --> 04:02.677
AND ENGAGED IN
SEXUAL RELATIONS WITH HER
IN YOUR LIFEGUARD TOWER.

04:04.156 --> 04:06.028
-SHE'S LYING, ALL RIGHT?
I DIDN'T TOUCH HER!

04:06.158 --> 04:07.464
-WHY WOULD SHE LIE?

04:08.335 --> 04:09.901
-SHE'S BRAGGING.

04:10.032 --> 04:12.077
-LIFEGUARDS ARE TROPHIES.

04:12.208 --> 04:13.992
-EDDIE, DID YOU KNOW
SHE'S 15 YEARS OLD?

04:14.123 --> 04:15.559
-YES.

04:16.255 --> 04:19.868
-LOOK, MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T
WAIVE YOUR RIGHT TO
HAVE AN ATTORNEY PRESENT.

04:20.521 --> 04:22.218
-I DON'T NEED ONE, GARNER.
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

04:22.349 --> 04:23.785
-[SHOUTS]
SHE SWEARS YOU DID!

04:24.394 --> 04:25.787
-FINE!
THEN IT'S HER WORD AGAINST MINE!

04:26.440 --> 04:28.529
-THAT'S RIGHT.
THE WORD OF A STREET PUNK,

04:28.659 --> 04:30.792
WHO WAS ARRESTED TWICE
AS A JUVENILE

04:30.922 --> 04:33.011
FOR SHOP-LIFTING
AND GRAND THEFT AUTO,

04:33.142 --> 04:35.492
VIOLATED PROBATION.
THE LIST GOES ON.

04:35.623 --> 04:36.972
-YEAH, WELL, IT'S AN OLD LIST.

04:37.102 --> 04:38.756
-[TELEPHONE RINGING]

04:38.887 --> 04:40.367
-[CLEARS THROAT]
-YEAH?

04:42.194 --> 04:43.587
RIGHT. THANKS.

04:45.067 --> 04:48.723
EDDIE, MITCH AND THE GUYS
HAVE POSTED BAIL FOR YOU.
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

04:48.853 --> 04:52.466
-YOU'LL BE ARRAIGNED
WITHIN 48 HOURS, SO DON'T MAKE
ANY VACATION PLANS.

04:52.596 --> 04:53.902
-EDDIE.

04:55.033 --> 04:56.078
GET A GOOD LAWYER.

05:00.082 --> 05:04.129
-EDDIE, I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT AS FAR AS EVERYBODY HERE
IS CONCERNED,

05:05.217 --> 05:06.567
YOU WERE SET UP.

05:09.091 --> 05:10.135
-BUT?

05:10.266 --> 05:11.398
-BUT...

05:12.486 --> 05:15.315
ACCORDING TO
DEPARTMENTAL REGULATIONS,

05:17.229 --> 05:20.320
YOU GOTTA BE SUSPENDED
PENDING THE OUTCOME
OF AN INVESTIGATION.

05:21.408 --> 05:22.844
-[SIGHS]

05:22.974 --> 05:24.541
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

05:26.804 --> 05:27.936
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, MITCH?

05:29.198 --> 05:31.722
IF A STRANGER'S OUT THERE
DROWNING, EVERYBODY'S ON IT.

05:32.854 --> 05:34.508
GUARD NEEDS HELP,

05:34.638 --> 05:36.684
BACKUP COMES FROM LAND, SEA,
AND AIR, IF HE NEEDS IT.

05:36.814 --> 05:38.860
BUT WHAT IF HE
REALLY NEEDS IT, HUH?

05:39.991 --> 05:42.037
I MEAN...

05:42.167 --> 05:44.735
WHAT IF HE'S THE ONE
WHO'S REALLY IN TROUBLE?
WHAT'S HIS BACKUP THEN?

05:44.866 --> 05:45.997
NOWHERE.

05:47.477 --> 05:50.524
"YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN, PAL.
SINK OR SWIM."
WELL...

05:52.569 --> 05:53.614
THANKS A LOT, MITCH.

05:54.179 --> 05:56.225
-YOU KNOW WHAT TO SAY.
SAY YOUR STORY, THAT'S ALL.

05:56.356 --> 05:57.357
-EDDIE.

05:57.487 --> 05:59.315
-WHY?
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS...

05:59.446 --> 06:01.143
-YOU STAY AWAY FROM MY DAUGHTER.
-DON'T LIE! TELL HIM.

06:01.273 --> 06:02.840
-TAKE IT EASY, HUH?
-MITCH, SHE'S LYING.

06:02.971 --> 06:04.320
I NEVER TOUCHED HER.
SHE'S A LIAR!

06:04.451 --> 06:06.540
-YOU'RE THE ONE WHO'S LYING!

06:06.670 --> 06:09.107
-COME HERE!
-I NEVER TOUCHED YOU.
YOU KNOW I NEVER TOUCHED YOU.

06:09.238 --> 06:10.892
-BRAD, GET HIM DOWNSTAIRS.

06:11.022 --> 06:12.415
-TELL HIM.
-GO ON.

06:12.546 --> 06:14.199
-YOU'RE A LIAR.

06:15.636 --> 06:17.551
-I WANT HIM ARRESTED
FOR ASSAULT.

06:17.681 --> 06:19.509
-YOU THREW THE FIRST PUNCH.
-[SHOUTS] NO!
I WANT HIM...

06:19.640 --> 06:21.337
-CALM DOWN!
COME ON NOW.

06:21.468 --> 06:22.643
COME INTO MY OFFICE.

06:47.581 --> 06:49.713
-DID THEY SAY HOW LONG
YOU'RE GONNA BE SUSPENDED?

06:50.410 --> 06:55.110
-INDEFINITELY, OR UNTIL
SOMETHING GOES BETTER FOR ME,
WHICH WILL NEVER HAPPEN.

06:56.938 --> 06:58.679
-NOBODY THINKS
YOU DID IT, EDDIE.

06:58.809 --> 07:01.595
-[EXHALES]
YOU PULLED YOUR HAND
AWFULLY QUICK

07:01.725 --> 07:03.945
WHEN YOU FOUND OUT
WHAT GARNER SAID, HUH?

07:05.294 --> 07:07.905
-THAT WAS A REFLEX. I'M SORRY.
I WISH I CAN TAKE IT BACK.

07:08.036 --> 07:09.907
-YEAH.
YOU KNOW,

07:10.517 --> 07:13.041
SOMETHING GOES WRONG, BUST ME.
BLAME ME FOR EVERYTHING.

07:13.171 --> 07:14.521
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, SHAUNI?

07:16.218 --> 07:18.481
-DON'T PULL AWAY
FROM ME, PLEASE.
-WHAT'S THE POINT?

07:18.612 --> 07:21.658
-HUH? YOU'RE OLD MAN IS GONNA
STOP YOU FROM SEEING ME
AS SOON AS HE FINDS OUT.

07:21.789 --> 07:23.268
-I'M NOT GONNA LET HIM.

07:23.399 --> 07:25.662
-EDDIE, COME ON...
-YOU DON'T GET IT, DO YA?

07:25.793 --> 07:28.230
YOU DON'T GET IT.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.753
IT'S THE STORY OF MY LIFE.
I DON'T KNOW WHO THE HELL
IS RIGHT IN THIS DAMN THING,

07:29.884 --> 07:31.146
BUT IT AIN'T GONNA BE
A HAPPY ENDING.

07:31.276 --> 07:33.409
SO, GET OUT WHILE YOU CAN.

07:35.019 --> 07:36.760
-DON'T LEAVE, EDDIE.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

07:36.891 --> 07:38.458
-[ANGRILY]
TO FIND SOME PLACE
WHERE I CAN BREATHE!

07:49.251 --> 07:50.774
-I'M AT THE END OF MY RAMP.

07:53.124 --> 07:55.431
-TURNER, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M SUPPOSED TO DO?

07:55.562 --> 07:57.172
I'M NOT SURE WHAT YOU WANT.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.392
-WHAT I WANT?

08:01.742 --> 08:03.134
HOW ABOUT A TIME MACHINE?

08:03.874 --> 08:05.876
-I WISH I COULD
MAKE ONE FOR YOU.

08:06.660 --> 08:07.965
-YOU CAN'T.

08:12.579 --> 08:13.971
-SHOULD WE ARM-WRESTLE?

08:15.016 --> 08:16.060
-MALE:
MEGAN.

08:17.366 --> 08:19.411
YOU WOULDN'T SEE ME,
SO I CAME TO SEE YOU.

08:20.238 --> 08:22.414
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE
GETTING CHILLY,
SO I BROUGHT YOU SOME TEA.

08:22.545 --> 08:23.807
-THANKS.

08:24.808 --> 08:27.724
ROB, THIS IS ERIC TURNER.
ERIC, THIS IS ROB CARLTON.

08:28.333 --> 08:29.639
-PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

08:33.424 --> 08:35.253
-HOPE YOU BROUGHT SWEET'N LOW.

08:36.080 --> 08:38.779
WHAT? ABOUT THREE PACKS, RIGHT?

08:39.344 --> 08:40.780
-ACTUALLY, I TAKE IT PLAIN NOW.

08:43.217 --> 08:44.741
-AMAZING HOW THINGS CHANGE.

08:49.616 --> 08:51.400
-WOULD YOU LIKE SOME?
IT'S CHAMOMILE.

08:54.011 --> 08:55.491
-UH, NO, THANKS.

08:58.494 --> 08:59.539
I BETTER GO.

09:08.069 --> 09:09.113
-HERE, LET ME GIVE YOU A HAND.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.462
-GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME!

09:16.425 --> 09:17.948
[EXCLAIMS]

09:24.085 --> 09:25.652
-TURNER!

09:25.782 --> 09:26.609
TURNER!

10:08.738 --> 10:09.913
-MALE:
MR. BUCHANNON?

10:12.350 --> 10:13.700
MR. BUCHANNON?

10:14.483 --> 10:16.267
-HOSPITAL ANNOUNCER:
DR. PRITCHETT TO EMERGENCY.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.052
DR. PRITCHETT TO EMERGENCY.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.357
-DR. KEN.

10:20.489 --> 10:21.403
HOW'S HE DOING?

10:21.533 --> 10:23.448
-WELL, HE'S STABLE.

10:23.579 --> 10:26.538
IN FACT, HE'S STRONG
CONSIDERING WHAT HE'S UNDERGONE.

10:27.496 --> 10:29.063
-CAN I SEE HIM?
-SURE.

10:29.803 --> 10:31.631
BUT I WANNA MAKE YOU
AWARE FIRST.

10:31.761 --> 10:33.937
I JUST TOLD ERIC HIS CONDITION.

10:34.982 --> 10:36.113
-WHICH IS?

10:36.984 --> 10:40.378
-[SIGHS]
FRAGMENTS OF BONE
HAVE IMPINGED HIS SPINAL CHORD.

10:41.771 --> 10:43.904
HE'S PARALYZED
FROM THE WAIST DOWN.

10:45.427 --> 10:46.341
-WHAT?

10:48.778 --> 10:49.953
WOW.

10:52.129 --> 10:54.392
WHAT ABOUT REHABILITATION,
AND, YOU KNOW, PHYSICAL THERAPY?

10:55.611 --> 10:58.701
-NO, I'M AFRAID THAT
THE PARALYSIS IS IRREVERSIBLE.

10:58.832 --> 11:00.616
-OH, COME ON, DOCTOR.
THIS GUY IS AN ATHLETE.

11:02.792 --> 11:04.141
-I'M SORRY.

11:05.882 --> 11:07.188
I'M VERY SORRY.

11:28.731 --> 11:30.385
-FEMALE NURSE: HI.
-HEY.

11:35.912 --> 11:39.655
-HEY, MITCH.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

11:40.961 --> 11:42.702
MEG SNUCK THIS IN FOR ME.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.095
CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT MY MUSIC.

11:45.226 --> 11:46.575
-RIGHT.

11:47.968 --> 11:48.882
HOW'RE YOU FEELING?

11:49.970 --> 11:51.406
-LIKE RACING.

11:53.364 --> 11:55.671
BUT THE DOC SAYS
I WONT BE ABLE TO
DO IT FOR A WHILE.

11:56.498 --> 11:57.325
-DR. KEN?

11:57.455 --> 12:00.415
-[CHUCKLES]
YEAH. WELL...

12:00.545 --> 12:03.331
HE USED THE WORD "NEVER,"
BUT, UH,

12:04.332 --> 12:06.943
HE DOESN'T KNOW THE HEART
OF A LIFEGUARD LIKE WE DO,
DOES HE?

12:07.074 --> 12:08.510
-OH, HE DOESN'T.

12:10.904 --> 12:12.035
-RIGHT.

12:13.558 --> 12:14.821
YOU BETTER KEEP WORKING OUT

12:15.647 --> 12:17.258
'CAUSE I'M GONNA BEAT YOU.

12:17.388 --> 12:20.478
-WELL, WON'T BE THE FIRST TIME,
WILL IT?

12:23.481 --> 12:24.613
-WHO WON THE OVERALL?

12:25.832 --> 12:26.920
-SORRY TO TELL YOU THIS.

12:29.226 --> 12:30.097
ZUMA.

12:33.535 --> 12:34.754
-[EXCITEDLY]
ALL RIGHT!

12:37.626 --> 12:41.151
-UH, MEGAN'S DOWNSTAIRS,
AND A WHOLE BUNCH
OF OTHER PEOPLE.

12:41.282 --> 12:42.413
THEY'RE ALL DYING TO SEE YOU.

12:43.893 --> 12:46.809
ARE YOU UP TO THAT?
I MEAN, CAN I BRING THEM UP?

12:46.940 --> 12:48.811
-YEAH. A VICTORY PARTY.

12:49.507 --> 12:50.552
LET'S DO IT.

12:50.682 --> 12:51.553
HEY, MITCH.

12:54.948 --> 12:56.036
DO ME A FAVOR, MITCH.

13:01.955 --> 13:03.957
GET RID OF THAT THING
FOR ME, WILL YA?

13:06.046 --> 13:08.396
-GOT IT.
IT'S OUTTA HERE.

13:55.443 --> 13:56.792
-SHAUNI.

13:56.923 --> 13:58.663
WHAT'RE YOU DOING HERE?

14:02.276 --> 14:03.843
PRETTY LATE, ISN'T IT?

14:09.022 --> 14:10.937
-I'M JUST HOPING EDDIE SHOWS UP.

14:11.851 --> 14:13.026
-TAKE IT EASY.

14:13.591 --> 14:15.637
EDDIE'S NOT THE FIRST LIFEGUARD
THIS HAS HAPPENED TO.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.509
I KNOW.
I REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED
TO CRAIG.

14:20.816 --> 14:21.730
-IT ALSO HAPPENED TO ME.

14:23.950 --> 14:25.299
QUITE A FEW YEARS AGO.

14:25.429 --> 14:26.866
-WHAT HAPPENED?

14:28.650 --> 14:30.870
-IT WAS SUMMER, '63.

14:32.697 --> 14:34.090
BEACH BOY MUSIC.

14:34.221 --> 14:36.788
LITTLE SURFER GIRLS
RUNNING ALL OVER THE PLACE.

14:37.311 --> 14:38.268
ANYWAY,

14:40.183 --> 14:41.706
THREE GIRLS MADE A BET

14:42.620 --> 14:44.622
ON WHO WAS GONNA
WIN MY AFFECTION.

14:44.753 --> 14:46.320
AT THE END OF SUMMER,

14:46.450 --> 14:47.669
THEY ALL CLAIMED VICTORY.

14:47.799 --> 14:48.800
-SO WHAT DID YOU DO?

14:48.931 --> 14:50.106
-I GOT THEM ALL TOGETHER.

14:50.237 --> 14:51.412
I CONFRONTED THEM.

14:51.934 --> 14:53.240
AND THE TRUTH WON OUT.

14:53.980 --> 14:55.024
LIKE IT ALWAYS DOES.

14:56.460 --> 14:59.594
THAT'S WHY EDDIE'S
GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
HE'S GONNA GET THROUGH IT.

15:00.203 --> 15:03.032
-I KNOW.
IT JUST HURTS THAT HE WANTS TO
GET THROUGH IT BY HIMSELF.

15:03.163 --> 15:04.120
-NO.

15:05.339 --> 15:07.080
HE WANTS TO GET THROUGH IT
WITH YOU.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.734
HE JUST NEEDS MORE TIME.

15:10.692 --> 15:11.911
-YOU REALLY THINK SO?

15:12.041 --> 15:13.216
-I KNOW SO.

15:13.347 --> 15:15.131
ALL RIGHT.
NOW, YOU GO ON HOME.

15:15.784 --> 15:17.829
'CAUSE IF EDDIE CALLS
OR SHOWS UP HERE,

15:17.960 --> 15:19.614
I'M GONNA HOGTIE HIM,
AND THEN I'M GONNA CALL YOU.
GO ON.

15:23.009 --> 15:25.359
-THANK YOU.
YOU'RE THE BEST.

15:29.102 --> 15:31.843
-MALE: SO AS SOON AS THE WIND
SWITCHES ON SHORE,
WE'RE OUT THERE.

15:31.974 --> 15:35.325
-ALL RIGHT.
-TAKE OFF FROM RIGHT OVER THERE,
THEN WE'RE GONE.

15:35.456 --> 15:36.239
-THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

15:36.370 --> 15:38.285
-[EXCLAIMS]

15:38.415 --> 15:40.026
THEN WE'LL GRAB THE SURF
AFTER WE EAT,
IF THERE'S ANY WAVES.

15:42.550 --> 15:43.812
-HEY, GUYS.

15:44.334 --> 15:45.857
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, HUH?

15:45.988 --> 15:47.076
HOW COME YOU'RE SITTING AROUND
ON YOUR BUTTS?

15:47.598 --> 15:49.513
WHAT, IT'S A LITTLE TOO
BLOWN OUT FOR YOU?

15:49.644 --> 15:51.733
-NAH, IT'S NOT FLYABLE
IN THIS WIND.

15:51.863 --> 15:53.735
SMASH YOU RIGHT
INTO THE ROCKS, MAN.

15:53.865 --> 15:55.345
-ONLY IF YOU GIVE INTO IT.

15:55.955 --> 15:56.868
LET ME USE YOUR RIG.

15:57.478 --> 15:59.436
-BIP.

15:59.567 --> 16:01.177
-COME ON, I'LL SHOW YOU
HOW TO HAVE THE FLIGHT
OF YOUR LIFE, MAN.

16:03.527 --> 16:08.358
COME ON.
IT'LL BE AN ADRENALINE RUSH
THAT'LL MAKE YOU POP.

16:08.489 --> 16:09.881
-SURE. WHY NOT?

16:10.708 --> 16:11.796
NORMAL.

