18:17.966 --> 18:20.490
♪ YOU'RE CRASH IN LIKE THE SEA BABY

18:20.621 --> 18:24.451
♪ OOH OOOOH
OOH OOH YEAH ♪

18:24.581 --> 18:28.498
♪ OOH OOH NO
DON'T WAKE ME UP NO ♪

18:28.629 --> 18:32.459
♪ OOH OOOOH
OOH OOH YEAH ♪

18:32.589 --> 18:35.505
♪ OOH OOOOH

18:36.289 --> 18:39.770
♪ OOH
THIS IS WHAT DREAMS ARE MADE OF ♪

18:39.901 --> 18:43.731
♪ RUNNING TO YOU I CAN'T GET ENOUGH

18:44.253 --> 18:47.430
♪ OOH
THIS IS WHAT DREAMS ARE MADE OF ♪

18:48.170 --> 18:51.347
♪ HOT RUSH READY TO FALL IN LOVE ♪

18:52.218 --> 18:57.005
♪ OOH OOH
DON'T WAKE ME UP ♪

19:00.313 --> 19:04.404
♪ OOH OOH
DON'T WAKE ME UP ♪

19:04.534 --> 19:07.842
-FLYING ON A DAY LIKE TODAY,
YOU'LL THINK YOU DIED
AND WENT TO HEAVEN.

19:25.555 --> 19:26.600
-OH, MY GOD!

19:30.821 --> 19:32.867
YEAH. PATCH ME THROUGH
TO MITCH, AND HURRY.

19:32.997 --> 19:35.652
THOSE ARE ODIOUS WINDS, MAN.
WHAT'RE YOU TRYING TO PROVE?

19:35.783 --> 19:38.438
-THAT YOU DON'T NEED LEGS
IF YOU GOT WINGS.

19:39.265 --> 19:40.657
-ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE READY FOR THIS?

19:41.310 --> 19:42.442
-YOU BET.

19:42.572 --> 19:44.357
-ALL RIGHT, MAN.
HERE WE GO.

19:46.010 --> 19:47.838
-ADIOS, AMIGO!

19:47.969 --> 19:51.973
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

20:33.971 --> 20:37.584
-[SIRENS BLARING]

20:54.296 --> 20:55.689
-HOW COULD YOU LET HIM GO?

20:55.819 --> 20:56.994
-HEY, THE DUDE'S A PRO.

20:57.125 --> 20:58.692
-THE DUDE'S OUT OF HIS MIND!

21:27.024 --> 21:28.417
DAMN IT!

21:29.157 --> 21:30.767
I NEED YOUR GLIDER.
-SURE.

21:39.428 --> 21:42.953
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

23:01.380 --> 23:02.424
-OKAY.

23:02.555 --> 23:03.338
OKAY.

23:03.469 --> 23:05.645
-[COUGHING]

23:12.216 --> 23:13.261
-IS HE OKAY?

23:13.392 --> 23:14.305
-HE'S OKAY.

23:16.395 --> 23:19.876
HEY. [SHOUTS]
HEY! HEY!

23:31.540 --> 23:32.585
-HEY.

23:34.021 --> 23:35.196
-NO LUCK, HUH?

23:35.762 --> 23:37.894
-I HAVE BEEN DRIVING AROUND
ALL NIGHT, MITCH.

23:38.025 --> 23:39.853
I'M WORRIED ABOUT HIM.
I MEAN, YOU KNOW HOW HE GETS.

23:39.983 --> 23:41.158
-YEAH.

23:41.898 --> 23:43.422
-DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THAT GIRL WORKS?

23:44.031 --> 23:46.599
-YEAH. SHE WORKS AT
THE BOATHOUSE RESTAURANT
ON THE PIER.

23:47.251 --> 23:49.384
I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT EDDIE.

23:50.080 --> 23:51.430
HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

23:52.779 --> 23:54.041
WHERE ELSE IS HE GONNA GO?

24:20.197 --> 24:23.940
♪ IT'S ANOTHER DAY IN THIS LIFE

24:25.507 --> 24:27.944
♪ WHERE DO YOU BEGIN?

24:29.859 --> 24:34.821
♪ SO MANY FACES, SO MANY PLACES

24:34.951 --> 24:38.912
♪ THERE'S A FIRE DEEP WITHIN

24:40.740 --> 24:45.614
♪ NOTHING'S LIKE IT USED TO BE ANYMORE

24:45.745 --> 24:48.182
♪ WOAH

24:49.183 --> 24:53.404
♪ AND TIME WAITS FOR NO ONE

24:54.971 --> 24:59.585
♪ STAND UP, YOU GOTTA PUT UP A FIGHT

24:59.715 --> 25:03.980
♪ STAND UP AND LET THE FLAMES IGNITE

25:04.111 --> 25:10.117
♪ STAND UP CUZ IT'S YOUR TIME

25:13.163 --> 25:17.733
♪ YOU'VE COME SO FAR

25:17.864 --> 25:21.955
♪ IT'S WHO YOU ARE

25:22.085 --> 25:24.697
♪ STAND UP

25:24.827 --> 25:28.527
♪ YOU,VE GOTTA PUT UP A FIGHT

26:17.445 --> 26:18.925
-TURNER, LOOK AT ME.

26:19.752 --> 26:20.796
LOOK AT ME!

26:20.927 --> 26:22.189
-NO, YOU LOOK AT ME.

26:23.494 --> 26:25.279
NOBODY LOOKS AT ME.

26:26.802 --> 26:30.458
THEY LOOK AT ME
AND SEE SOMETHING ELSE.
THEY DON'T SEE WHO I AM!

26:34.941 --> 26:38.118
I'M JUST AFRAID
OF BECOMING WHAT PEOPLE SEE.

26:38.771 --> 26:39.902
-WELL, I DON'T BUY THAT.

26:40.599 --> 26:42.122
YOU KNOW WHAT I SEE?

26:42.252 --> 26:44.124
THAT YOU'RE TRYING
TO PROVE SOMETHING.

26:46.605 --> 26:49.738
YOU DON'T HAVE TO PROVE
ANYTHING TO ME, TURNER.

26:55.004 --> 26:56.136
-DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA?

26:57.267 --> 26:58.573
WHEN I CAME BACK,

26:59.530 --> 27:02.098
I DIDN'T EXPECT YOU
TO STILL BE IN LOVE WITH ME.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.972
BUT THEN I SAW YOU, AND...

27:07.974 --> 27:10.716
AND ALL THE MEMORIES STARTED...

27:11.978 --> 27:13.762
COMING BACK, AND...

27:15.198 --> 27:18.549
SUDDENLY I FELT LIKE MAYBE
THINGS COULD BE LIKE THEY WERE.

27:21.770 --> 27:23.206
-WHEN YOU GOT HURT,

27:23.859 --> 27:25.600
ALL I COULD THINK ABOUT WAS YOU.

27:26.209 --> 27:27.994
WHAT COULD I DO FOR YOU?

27:29.125 --> 27:32.346
I WOULD'VE SACRIFICED EVERYTHING
TO BE THERE FOR YOU.

27:33.477 --> 27:35.741
BUT YOU TOTALLY SHUT ME OUT.

27:39.788 --> 27:42.225
-I JUST DIDN'T WANNA
PUT YOU THROUGH MY PAIN.

27:43.618 --> 27:45.794
-DON'T YOU THINK
THAT SHOULD'VE BEEN MY DECISION?

27:45.925 --> 27:47.796
-NO, IT HAD TO BE MINE!

27:48.710 --> 27:51.757
LIKE IT'S MY DECISION TO GO BACK
TO SAN DIEGO TOMORROW.

27:51.887 --> 27:53.976
-BUT THE JOB,
IT'LL BE GOOD FOR YOU...

27:54.107 --> 27:55.586
-[ANGRILY]
I CAN'T HANDLE A JOB, MEG!

27:55.717 --> 27:56.979
-YES, YOU CAN!

27:57.110 --> 27:59.155
-NO, I CAN'T!
DON'T DO THIS TO ME!

28:08.425 --> 28:10.514
-I'LL STILL BE HERE
FOR YOU, TURNER.

28:11.341 --> 28:13.213
ANYTIME YOU NEED A FRIEND.

28:18.218 --> 28:20.350
-AND WHAT IF I NEED
MORE THAN A FRIEND?

28:24.050 --> 28:25.355
-I DON'T KNOW, TURNER.

28:27.009 --> 28:28.663
I JUST DON'T KNOW.

28:57.561 --> 28:58.475
-MITCH:
YOUR MOVE.

28:59.955 --> 29:01.130
-IT'S MY BUDDY!

29:02.653 --> 29:04.090
-OH, I AM YOUR FRIEND.

29:04.786 --> 29:06.832
-A REAL FRIEND WOULDN'T HAVE
TURNED HIS BACK ON ME.

29:08.834 --> 29:11.314
-EDDIE, PEOPLE ARE
LOOKING FOR YOU, YOU KNOW?

29:11.967 --> 29:13.055
WORRIED.

29:14.143 --> 29:16.580
-TELL 'EM YOU FOUND ME
AND I'M DOING JUST FINE.

29:19.583 --> 29:21.455
-YOU KNOW, YOU MUST'VE BEEN
REAL GOOD AT TRACK AT SCHOOL.

29:21.585 --> 29:23.022
-AND WHAT THE HELL'S
THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

29:23.152 --> 29:24.240
-YOU'RE ALWAYS RUNNING.

29:25.676 --> 29:27.766
-MITCH, I DIDN'T DESERVE
WHAT HAPPENED TO ME, OKAY?

29:27.896 --> 29:29.985
-OH, GIVE ME A BREAK!

29:30.116 --> 29:31.726
WHO DESERVES ANYTHING?

29:31.857 --> 29:33.946
DO YOU THINK TURNER DESERVED
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

29:34.685 --> 29:35.861
AT LEAST YOU CAN RUN.

29:35.991 --> 29:37.297
-WELL, I GUESS I'M LUCKY.
-LUCKY?

29:38.211 --> 29:39.081
YOU'RE BLESSED.

29:40.343 --> 29:42.606
YOU GOT SOMEONE IN THIS WORLD
WHO REALLY CARES ABOUT YOU.

29:44.347 --> 29:45.784
DON'T BLOW IT WITH HER.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.527
-HEY, MITCH.
-WHAT?

29:52.051 --> 29:53.139
-YOU KNOW WHERE SHE IS?

29:55.358 --> 29:56.969
-YEAH. SHE'S HEADED
TOWARDS THE PIER.

30:55.766 --> 30:56.898
-CAROLINE.

30:57.420 --> 30:59.379
MY NAME'S SHAUNI.
YOUR BOSS SAID
YOU WERE OUT HERE.

31:00.815 --> 31:01.816
-YOUR EDDIE'S GIRLFRIEND.

31:02.991 --> 31:04.079
-HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

31:05.428 --> 31:07.082
-NOT SINCE YESTERDAY.

31:08.518 --> 31:09.998
-WELL, I THINK THAT
YOU AND I NEED TO TALK.

31:11.217 --> 31:13.436
-WELL, LOOK,
MY DAD'S GONNA BE HERE
ANY MINUTE.

31:14.611 --> 31:16.831
-WELL, THAT DOESN'T GIVE US
MUCH TIME THEN, DOES IT?

31:18.659 --> 31:20.400
-PLEASE JUST LEAVE ME ALONE.

31:21.836 --> 31:25.492
-CAROLINE, LOOK.
I KNOW HOW HARD IT IS
TO BE THE NEW GIRL ON THE BEACH.

31:25.622 --> 31:28.625
AND BELIEVE ME,
I KNOW HOW IMPORTANT IT IS
TO BE ACCEPTED.

31:31.367 --> 31:33.369
SOONER OR LATER,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
TELL THE TRUTH.

31:33.500 --> 31:34.805
BECAUSE THE LONGER
YOU PUT IT OFF,

31:34.936 --> 31:36.590
THE MORE PEOPLE
YOU'RE GONNA HURT.

31:37.591 --> 31:39.898
-[CRIES]
ALL YOU WANT IS TO GET
YOUR BOYFRIEND OFF THE HOOK.

31:40.986 --> 31:42.422
YOU DON'T CARE ABOUT ME.

31:42.552 --> 31:43.814
-IT'S NOT TRUE.
I DO CARE.

31:45.381 --> 31:46.905
-[CRIES]
NOBODY DOES.

31:47.775 --> 31:49.255
-CAROLINE, COME ON.

31:49.385 --> 31:51.300
-MY FATHER THINKS I'M A WHORE.

31:51.431 --> 31:53.868
-LISTEN, IF YOU JUST
TELL THE TRUTH,
THEN HE WON'T.

31:55.043 --> 31:57.611
-AND EVERYONE WILL KNOW
I'M NOTHING.

31:58.351 --> 32:00.309
I'M NOTHING!
I'M NOTHING!

32:00.440 --> 32:01.658
-CAROLINE, DON'T!

32:01.789 --> 32:04.357
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

34:06.261 --> 34:08.481
-GET OFF HER!
I SAID LEAVE HER ALONE!

34:08.610 --> 34:10.135
LEAVE HER ALONE.
-[SHAUNI SHOUTS]
STOP IT!

34:10.264 --> 34:12.311
STOP IT!
HE'S TRYING TO SAVE HER!

34:12.440 --> 34:14.748
STOP IT!
YOU DAUGHTER JUST
JUMPED OFF THE PIER.

34:16.489 --> 34:17.838
-WHY?

34:17.967 --> 34:19.534
-MAYBE BECAUSE
SHE COULDN'T LIE ANYMORE.

34:20.362 --> 34:21.536
-GIVE ME YOUR JACKET.

34:22.234 --> 34:23.844
-I'M SORRY I LIED.

34:24.540 --> 34:26.760
I DIDN'T MEAN TO GET YOU
IN SO MUCH TROUBLE.

34:36.378 --> 34:37.639
-I'M SORRY.

34:38.859 --> 34:40.078
I'M SORRY.

34:41.643 --> 34:42.949
I HAD NO IDEA.

34:57.747 --> 35:01.186
-MITCH, YOU EVER JUST
WANNA GET ON A BOAT
AND JUST SAIL AWAY?

35:03.884 --> 35:05.581
-YOU KNOW,
I SHOULD'VE LET YOU DROWN.

35:06.582 --> 35:08.976
I WOULDN'T HAVE TO LISTEN
TO ALL THIS NONSENSE.

35:11.326 --> 35:14.895
-OH, WHAT?
[MOCKINGLY]
WHAT, ARE YOU ANGRY WITH ME?

35:15.025 --> 35:15.939
YOU ANGRY WITH ME?

35:16.592 --> 35:17.463
YOU MAD AT ME?
GO AHEAD, HIT ME.

35:17.593 --> 35:18.942
HIT ME.
GO AHEAD, HIT ME!

35:19.073 --> 35:20.988
-NO!

35:21.119 --> 35:22.250
'CAUSE I KNOW YOU WON'T
HIT ME BACK 'CAUSE
I'M IN THIS CHAIR.

35:22.381 --> 35:23.599
-I'LL KNOCK YOU
RIGHT ON YOUR ASS.

35:24.513 --> 35:25.732
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

35:25.862 --> 35:27.473
YOU AFRAID THAT WHEN I HIT YOU,

35:27.603 --> 35:29.170
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO USE
YOUR CHAIR AS AN EXCUSE ANYMORE?

35:29.301 --> 35:30.519
GO AHEAD, MAN!

35:34.175 --> 35:36.090
-YOU THINK YOU KNOW EVERYTHING,
DON'T YOU?

35:36.221 --> 35:37.657
DON'T YOU?

35:39.528 --> 35:40.486
-ALL RIGHT!

35:42.314 --> 35:43.837
YOU SAY YOU LOVE THE WATER,

35:43.967 --> 35:45.795
THEN WHY DON'T YOU TAKE
THE JOB, MAN?

35:46.492 --> 35:47.971
BE A SWIM COACH.

35:48.842 --> 35:50.931
-[BOTH STRUGGLING]

35:53.499 --> 35:54.761
-KNOCK IT OFF!

35:54.891 --> 35:56.023
KNOCK IT OFF!

35:56.154 --> 35:57.546
NOW, SHUT UP AND LISTEN TO ME!

35:58.808 --> 36:00.984
YOU GOT AN OPPORTUNITY
TO INSPIRE KIDS!

36:01.811 --> 36:03.639
YOU CAN TEACH THEM, MAN!

36:03.770 --> 36:06.164
YOU CAN TEACH THEM.
NO OBSTACLE IS TOO BIG
TO OVERCOME.

36:07.382 --> 36:08.949
YOU CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE
IN THEIR LIVES.

36:10.820 --> 36:14.346
TURNER, YOU'VE GOT MORE COURAGE
THAN ANY MAN I'VE EVER MET.

36:15.085 --> 36:16.696
WILL YOU JUST USE IT?

36:23.181 --> 36:25.313
-YOU COULD ALWAYS DO THIS TO ME,
COULDN'T YOU, MITCH?

36:26.271 --> 36:27.533
IT'S BECAUSE I LOVE YOU, MAN.

36:29.230 --> 36:30.405
I LOVE YOU LIKE A BROTHER.

36:48.641 --> 36:49.468
-HEY, MITCH.

36:49.598 --> 36:51.121
-YEAH?

36:51.252 --> 36:53.211
-I'M STARTING TO FEEL
PRETTY SILLY HERE.

36:53.950 --> 36:56.779
PEOPLE ARE LOOKING AT US.
[LAUGHS]

37:21.151 --> 37:23.415
COME ON.
I'LL RACE YOU TILL
THE END OF THE PIER.

37:39.213 --> 37:44.697
-LISTEN, WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE, UH, GRAB SOMETHING TO EAT?
GO DOWN TO THE PALISADES.

37:44.827 --> 37:46.786
-I'D LOVE IT.

37:46.916 --> 37:48.440
LET'S TAKE A WALK
ON THE BEACH FIRST
AND WATCH THE SUNSET.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.224
-PERFECT.
-YEAH.

37:56.665 --> 37:57.536
-CAN I COME UP?

38:00.060 --> 38:01.409
PLEASE, JUST FOR A MINUTE.

38:02.062 --> 38:03.281
-SURE.

38:07.850 --> 38:09.765
-I JUST CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.

38:09.896 --> 38:11.376
-I'M MOVING BACK TO OHIO.

38:11.506 --> 38:13.291
-I HOPE YOU'LL BE HAPPY THERE.

38:13.943 --> 38:14.988
-ME TOO.

38:19.732 --> 38:21.864
EDDIE. [SIGHS]

38:21.995 --> 38:24.389
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW SORRY I AM
ABOUT WHAT I DID TO YOU.

38:26.913 --> 38:29.263
I NEVER MEANT FOR IT
TO GET SO OUT OF HAND.

38:32.005 --> 38:33.136
I REALLY DIDN'T.

38:37.053 --> 38:38.359
-GOOD LUCK IN OHIO.

38:41.841 --> 38:42.842
-DO YOU FORGIVE ME?

38:46.715 --> 38:47.977
-HE DOES.

38:48.630 --> 38:50.023
IT'S JUST HARD TO SAY.

38:52.417 --> 38:53.983
-WELL, I CAN'T BLAME YOU
FOR HATING ME.

38:57.683 --> 39:01.600
WELL, THANKS, YOU KNOW,
FOR NOT LETTING ME DROWN.

39:05.821 --> 39:06.779
BYE.

39:08.998 --> 39:10.348
-CAROLINE.

39:18.094 --> 39:21.097
[SIGHS DEEPLY]
LOOK, I KNOW THAT YOU...

39:21.968 --> 39:24.623
YOU DIDN'T MEAN FOR THINGS
TO HAPPEN THE WAY THEY DID.

39:26.886 --> 39:29.410
BUT YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO DO
SOMETHING SO STUPID
JUST TO JOIN A CLIQUE.

39:32.152 --> 39:33.371
AND, HEY,

39:34.850 --> 39:36.809
NOTHING'S WORTH
KILLING YOURSELF FOR.

39:37.418 --> 39:38.811
YOU UNDERSTAND?

39:43.598 --> 39:46.035
-MY DAD SAID THAT I CAN GO
SEE SOMEONE.

39:47.254 --> 39:49.082
I GUESS A PSYCHOLOGIST
OR SOMETHING.

39:49.735 --> 39:51.214
HE'D COME WITH ME, SO...

39:52.346 --> 39:53.565
-GOOD.

39:55.262 --> 39:56.481
WELL...

39:59.266 --> 40:01.094
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF NOW.

40:03.488 --> 40:05.141
-TELL SHAUNI SHE'S LUCKY.

40:23.377 --> 40:24.552
-[CLEARS THROAT]

40:28.426 --> 40:29.992
SHE SAID YOU WERE LUCKY.

40:31.559 --> 40:32.560
-I AM.

40:39.088 --> 40:40.960
-I'M THE ONE THAT'S LUCKY.

41:43.413 --> 41:46.025
-["CURRENT OF LOVE" PLAYING]
